@vitaly-krugl Do you know how to "configure bash such that a failure in any link in the pipe causes the result of the pipe to be deemed as failure"?

According to [bash doc about pipeline](http://www.gnu.org/software/bash/manual/bash.html#Pipelines), it seems `set -o pipefail` would do the trick?

