You should also deal with the regex_entities=None right here, not later.  So:

if regex_entities is None:
    self.regex_entities = []
else:
    self.regex_entities = regex_entities

Or, we could make `charset` a property of the `resource.{Static,Dynamic}` classes instead of a global configuration value. That probably fits better with our evolution away from an app server towards being just a library.

```python
USE_DEFAULT_CHARSET = object()

class Static(object):
    charset = None
    def __init__(self, ..., charset=USE_CLASS_DEFAULT_CHARSET):
        pass

class Dynamic(Simplate):
    charset = 'UTF-8'
    def __init__(self, ..., charset=USE_CLASS_DEFAULT_CHARSET):
        pass
```

I have a slight preference to change from 

```
if (kind matches) {
  do_stuff();
}
```

to

```
if (! kind matches) {
  continue;
}
do_stuff();
```
